A general view of the outside of a COVID-19 ward at  Hospital in Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa is still seeing a decline in new COVID-19 infections. Only 933 new cases were recorded over the last 24 hours. This brings the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa to 1,530,966. READ: COVID-19 origins report postponed, likely due next week: WHO Regrettably, though, 139 more people have died. The recovery rate stands at 95-percent and the country has 21,405 active cases. Over 157,000 vaccines have been administered.  #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 16 March.
